     * Mediations

Mediations

   To help visitors to the Bpi to make the best use of its resources and
   services and to assist them on a daily basis, the Library offers, in
   addition to its cultural events and remote services, a range of
   mediation services on-site, that are accessible free of charge:

     * Tours of the Library and of the exhibitions
     * Workshops
     * Special services
     * Selected documents and special show spaces

   The Librarians are present at each information desk to orient you,
   inform you and help you in your document research.
   Don’t hesitate to ask them!

Tours

   For new arrivals or long-standing regulars, alone or in a group,
   teachers or members of an association, the Library offers a whole range
   of free tours, with or without a reservation and adapted to the...
   Tours Photo Delphine Nicolas, Bpi, [CC-By-NC-ND 2.0]

Workshops

   The Bpi regularly holds workshops for learning and creativity in such
   varied activities as foreign languages, job searches, making video and
   audio recordings, digital technologies and information tech...
   Workshops Atelier©Bpi/Vinciane Verguethen

Special services

   In order to provide a rapid response tailored to all our visitors’
   questions on different subjects, the Bpi has concluded partnerships
   with several associations. You will be put in touch with an exper...
   Special services photo Delphine Nicolas, Bpi, (cc-By-NC-ND 2.0)

Salons et sélections documentaires

   To enable the public to discover the variety of the collections of the
   Bpi, the librarians regularly select documents in connection with
   current events or the events offered by the Bpi.
   Salons et sélections documentaires Salon Sciences et technique,
   Caroline Uhland, Bpi [CC-BY-NC-ND 2.0]
